# Core Coding Standards

## General Principles

- **Single responsibility**: One class/function does one thing well
- **DRY**: Don't repeat yourself; extract shared logic
- **Meaningful names**: Variables, methods, and classes must clearly convey intent
- **Immutability**: Prefer `final` fields and immutable data where possible
- **Fail fast**: Validate inputs and fail immediately with clear errors (see fail-fast rule)

## Java Conventions

- Use `@Override` when implementing/overriding methods
- Prefer `Objects.requireNonNull()` for null checks on parameters
- Use `@Nullable` / `@NonNull` annotations when available
- Avoid magic numbers; use named constants
- Keep methods short (< 30 lines); extract when longer

## Code Quality

- No empty catch blocks; log and rethrow or handle explicitly
- Avoid `catch (Exception e)`; catch specific exceptions
- Use try-with-resources for `Closeable` / `AutoCloseable`
- Document public APIs with Javadoc
